
[1]pertinent

   PER'TINENT, a. [L. pertinens.] Related to the subject or matter in

   hand; just to the purpose; adapted to the end proposed; apposite; not
   foreign to the thing intended. We say, he used an argument not
   pertinent to his subject or design. The discourse abounds with
   pertinent remarks. He gave pertinent answers to the questions.

   1. Regarding; concerning; belonging. [Little used.]
